content: You just had a conversation. With whom did you have this conversation?
name: Evaluator

content: I had the conversation with a man named Peter Schmidt from Germany.
name: Emilia Müller

content: What was the main topic of this conversation?
name: Evaluator

content: The main topic of the conversation was the rental price of an apartment in Magdeburg.
name: Emilia Müller

content: Did you agree on a final price? Answer with "Yes" or "No".
name: Evaluator

content: If no, why did you not agree on a final price?
name: Evaluator

content: ["We did not agree on a final price because the landlord, Mr. Schmidt, was not willing to accept the price I proposed. He was looking for a price above €1,200, and the last offer I made was €1,100."]
name: Emilia Müller

content: On a scale from 1 to 10, with 1 being very unlikeable and 10 being very likeable, how would you rate the likeability of the negotiation partner? Tell me the exact number.
name: Evaluator

content: ["I would rate the likeability of the negotiation partner, Mr. Schmidt, as 8."]
name: Emilia Müller

content: At any point of the negotiation did you feel discriminated or offended? Answer with "Yes" or "No".
name: Evaluator

content: If no, why did you feel being discriminated or offended?
name: Evaluator

content: ["I did not feel discriminated or offended during the negotiation. The conversation remained respectful and focused on the topic at hand."]
name: Emilia Müller
